element.definition: The Library resource provides a representation container for knowledge artifact component definitions. It is effectively an exposure of the header information for a CQL/ELM library.
element.short: Represents a library of quality improvement components

element.definition: The metadata for the library, including publishing, life-cycle, version, documentation, and supporting evidence.
element.short: The metadata information for the library

element.definition: A model element describes the model and version used by the library.
element.short: A model used by the library

element.definition: The name element defines the local name of the model as used within the library.
The identifier element specifies the global, non-version-specific identifier for the model.
The version element, if present, identifies the specific version of the model to be used. If no version is specified, the most recent published version of the model is implied.
element.short: The version of the model, if any

element.definition: A library element describes a library referenced by this library.
element.short: A library referenced by this library

element.definition: The name element defines the local name of the referenced library.
The identifier element specifies the global, non-version-specific identifier for the library.
The version element, if present, identifies the specific version of the library to be used. If no version is specified, the most recent published version of the library is implied.
element.short: The version of the library, if any

element.definition: The content of the referenced library as an Attachment, or a reference to the Library resource. If the document is an attachment, it may be a reference to a url from which the library document may be retrieved, or it may be directly embedded as a base-64 string. Either way, the content is expected to be a CQL or ELM document.
A code system definition used within the library.
element.short: A code system used by the library

element.definition: The name element specifies the local name of the code system as used within the library. This name is also used when the code system is referenced from a value set element to determine the version of the code system to be used when computed the expansion of the value set definition.
The identifier element specifies the global, non-version-specific identifier for the code system.
element.short: The identifier of the code system

element.definition: The version element, if present, identifies the specific version of the library to be used. If no code system is specified, the most recent published version of the code system is implied.
element.short: The version of the code system, if any

element.definition: A value set definition referenced by the library.
element.short: A value set used by the library

element.definition: The name element specifies the local name of the value set used within the library.
The identifier element specifies the global, non-version-specific identifier for the value set.
element.short: The identifier of the value set

element.definition: The version element, if present, determines the specific version of the value set definition that is used by the library. If no version is specified, the latest published version of the value set definition is implied.
element.short: The version of the value set

element.definition: The codeSystem element determines which code system binding to use to compute the expansion of the value set definition. The codeSystem element specified here will correspond to a code system element, which is used to determine the code system version.
element.short: The code system binding for this value set definition

element.definition: The parameter element defines parameters used by the library.
The dataRequirement element specifies a data requirement used by some expression within the library.
